1
00:00:17,583 --> 00:00:27,541
♪

2
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:33,166
He's from Fairy Tail.

3
00:00:33,250 --> 00:00:35,833
Yeah. But why?

4
00:00:39,166 --> 00:00:42,291
You really don't wanna tangle
with our master, you runt.

5
00:00:42,375 --> 00:00:44,125
That guy's
gonna get murdered.

6
00:00:44,208 --> 00:00:46,291
Yeah, I don't
wanna watch this.

7
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:22,166
[JIEMMA] Did you truly come here
to challenge me? Very foolish.

8
00:02:22,250 --> 00:02:24,583
I came here to teach you not
to turn your back on people

9
00:02:24,666 --> 00:02:28,458
you're supposed to care for.
So you'd better listen.

10
00:02:28,541 --> 00:02:31,250
[ROGUE] Is he
talking about Yukino?

11
00:02:31,333 --> 00:02:33,125
[STING] Where does he get off?

12
00:02:33,208 --> 00:02:36,916
How our guild operates is
none of his damn business.

13
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:39,166
[JIEMMA] I don't know
what you're talking about.

14
00:02:39,250 --> 00:02:41,500
But it sounds to me
like you think everyone else

15
00:02:41,583 --> 00:02:44,625
should behave by your
personal moral code.

16
00:02:44,708 --> 00:02:47,416
How the hell do you not
know what I'm talking about?

17
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:51,041
Hey Doebengal.
Deal with this intruder.

18
00:02:51,125 --> 00:02:52,250
Yes, Sir.

19
00:02:52,333 --> 00:02:54,458
What, are you scared?

20
00:02:54,541 --> 00:02:56,041
I don't feel
like wasting my time

21
00:02:56,125 --> 00:02:58,416
disposing of an insect like you.

22
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:01,458
I am the master of this guild,
so if you wish to challenge me,

23
00:03:01,541 --> 00:03:05,041
you must prove yourself
to be a worthy adversary.

24
00:03:07,291 --> 00:03:09,208
[HAPPY] Pandemonium!

25
00:03:10,833 --> 00:03:13,000
Don't hide behind
your flunkies; fight me!

26
00:03:13,083 --> 00:03:15,083
[DOBENGAL] I won't
let you near our master!

27
00:03:23,875 --> 00:03:25,416
[DOBENGAL] Although I may
not be participating in

28
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:28,625
the Grand Magic
Games this year...

29
00:03:28,708 --> 00:03:30,541
[DOBENGAL] I am just as
skilled in battle as those

30
00:03:30,625 --> 00:03:32,333
who represent our guild.

31
00:03:33,458 --> 00:03:36,375
[DOBENGAL] Now you will taste
the true power of Sabertooth!

32
00:03:39,208 --> 00:03:41,083
You're hiding too?

33
00:03:45,208 --> 00:03:46,458
[DOBENGAL] I suggest
you leave at once

34
00:03:46,541 --> 00:03:49,541
or face the consequences! Now!

35
00:03:49,625 --> 00:03:51,083
[NATSU] Outta my way!

36
00:03:52,583 --> 00:03:55,166
[NATSU] I ain't got
business with you, pal!

37
00:03:57,333 --> 00:03:58,416
[SABERTOOTH GUY 166A] Holy crap!

38
00:03:58,500 --> 00:03:59,833
[SABERTOOTH GUY 166B]
He beat Dobengal?

39
00:03:59,916 --> 00:04:01,333
Whoa!

40
00:04:01,416 --> 00:04:02,916
He just took out one
of the toughest guys

41
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,708
in our guild like
he was nothin'!

42
00:04:04,791 --> 00:04:06,458
[JIEMMA growls]

43
00:04:06,541 --> 00:04:08,458
Master. I'll take him.

44
00:04:08,541 --> 00:04:10,416
You'll stay
out of this!

45
00:04:11,166 --> 00:04:14,458
[JIEMMA] No one in my guild
has your kind of spirit, boy.

46
00:04:14,541 --> 00:04:16,458
It's interesting.

47
00:04:22,375 --> 00:04:25,000
But spirit is not enough.

48
00:04:38,250 --> 00:04:41,708
[NATSU yells]

49
00:04:52,791 --> 00:04:57,500
[NATSU] Lightning Flame
Dragon. Firing Hammer!

50
00:04:58,750 --> 00:05:08,708
♪

51
00:05:16,958 --> 00:05:19,375
Minerva!

52
00:05:19,458 --> 00:05:20,875
Milady?

53
00:05:25,958 --> 00:05:27,500
Certainly you'll agree.

54
00:05:27,583 --> 00:05:30,458
This little quarrel of
ours has gone too far.

55
00:05:30,541 --> 00:05:31,833
What?

56
00:05:31,916 --> 00:05:35,625
How dare you get in my way!
This does not concern you.

57
00:05:35,708 --> 00:05:36,833
Please forgive me.

58
00:05:36,916 --> 00:05:38,250
[MINERVA] You could
easily defeat this man,

59
00:05:38,333 --> 00:05:41,416
so I'm not doing this
for your sake, father.

60
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:43,250
[NATSU] He's your dad?

61
00:05:43,333 --> 00:05:45,125
But we must take into
consideration how this

62
00:05:45,208 --> 00:05:48,000
altercation would appear
to the outside world.

63
00:05:48,083 --> 00:05:49,666
Despite the fact
that you are clearly

64
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:51,333
the aggressor in this situation,

65
00:05:51,416 --> 00:05:53,500
our master killing
another competitor

66
00:05:53,583 --> 00:05:55,833
would leave Sabertooth
in an awkward position,

67
00:05:55,916 --> 00:05:57,500
to say the very least.

68
00:05:57,583 --> 00:06:00,833
[MINERVA] It would certainly
put a damper on the games.

69
00:06:00,916 --> 00:06:02,166
You know what I think?

70
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:04,416
You're scared of seeing
this geezer get put down!

71
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:07,000
[MINERVA] You have enraged
both my father and his men.

72
00:06:07,083 --> 00:06:08,500
And they are not
the types to take

73
00:06:08,583 --> 00:06:11,083
this kind of
provocation lightly.

74
00:06:11,166 --> 00:06:13,875
What do you say?
Will you allow me to resolve

75
00:06:13,958 --> 00:06:16,666
this unpleasantness
in a peaceful manner?

76
00:06:16,750 --> 00:06:18,583
[grunts]

77
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:23,625
[MINERVA] Be aware. That is
also the only way your kitten

78
00:06:23,708 --> 00:06:25,666
will be returned
to you unharmed.

79
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:27,250
[wailing]

80
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:28,833
Happy!

81
00:06:28,916 --> 00:06:32,583
[HAPPY crying] Sorry, Natsu!

82
00:06:32,666 --> 00:06:34,541
Damn it!

83
00:06:34,625 --> 00:06:36,291
[MINERVA] You seem to have
taken out your anger on

84
00:06:36,375 --> 00:06:39,333
quite a few of our members.
But I am willing to overlook

85
00:06:39,416 --> 00:06:42,500
this incident entirely,
if you'll cooperate.

86
00:06:42,583 --> 00:06:44,416
Behave like a grownup
and we can continue

87
00:06:44,500 --> 00:06:46,583
the games like nothing happened.

88
00:06:46,666 --> 00:06:51,666
[growling lowly]

89
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:53,791
[crying]

90
00:06:53,875 --> 00:06:56,791
Oh, Natsu!

91
00:06:56,875 --> 00:06:59,916
[HAPPY] I'm sorry. They
caught me by surprise!

92
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,791
Aw. Don't worry, little buddy.

93
00:07:01,875 --> 00:07:05,291
I should be apologizing for
leaving you behind like that.

94
00:07:05,375 --> 00:07:07,291
It's okay!

95
00:07:08,125 --> 00:07:09,458
Let's get outta here.

96
00:07:09,541 --> 00:07:11,416
[HAPPY] Aye.

97
00:07:13,416 --> 00:07:16,291
You've got some serious
guts for such a fool.

98
00:07:16,375 --> 00:07:19,333
We can settle this matter once
and for all inside the arena.

99
00:07:19,416 --> 00:07:21,833
Where we'll
show you no mercy.

100
00:07:23,625 --> 00:07:27,125
[NATSU] Fine, but
you'll never beat us.

101
00:07:27,208 --> 00:07:29,375
We're at a whole other level.

102
00:07:34,125 --> 00:07:38,375
'Cause a real guild...
treats its members like family.

103
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:41,208
[NATSU] That's why
I came here tonight.

104
00:07:47,791 --> 00:07:50,000
[ROGUE] He may be right,
but that's not the way

105
00:07:50,083 --> 00:07:52,333
we treat each other here.

106
00:07:54,375 --> 00:07:59,875
[STING] That was crazy. He's way
stronger than I ever thought.

107
00:07:59,958 --> 00:08:02,250
Hey! I call
first game tomorrow!

108
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:04,250
And I'm gonna make sure
those Fairy Tail punks

109
00:08:04,333 --> 00:08:06,041
pay for what they did!

110
00:08:06,125 --> 00:08:09,208
Your Black Lightning shall
make their very souls tremble.

111
00:08:09,291 --> 00:08:11,125
Indeed, we shall
respond accordingly

112
00:08:11,208 --> 00:08:13,416
to this act
of disrespect.

113
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:16,083
[MINERVA] Although I must admit
disturbances such as these

114
00:08:16,166 --> 00:08:18,458
do keep things exciting.

115
00:08:18,541 --> 00:08:21,416
And Since Yukino
is no longer with us...

116
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:24,916
I shall take it upon
myself to fill her vacancy.

117
00:08:27,958 --> 00:08:29,500
What? You went
and picked a fight

118
00:08:29,583 --> 00:08:31,458
with the master of Sabertooth?

119
00:08:31,541 --> 00:08:33,500
Yeah. But I had to
stop before I really

120
00:08:33,583 --> 00:08:35,208
got a chance to lay into him.

121
00:08:35,291 --> 00:08:37,666
That geezer's lucky that
I'm such a reasonable guy.

122
00:08:37,750 --> 00:08:39,791
No, I'm the
reason he stopped.

123
00:08:39,875 --> 00:08:42,416
It's because I let
those jerks kidnap me.

124
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:43,791
Don't be ridiculous.

125
00:08:43,875 --> 00:08:46,000
It's far better that
it ended that way.

126
00:08:46,083 --> 00:08:49,041
Seriously. If Natsu
had actually injured

127
00:08:49,125 --> 00:08:51,125
anybody on their team,
our entire guild could've

128
00:08:51,208 --> 00:08:53,041
been kicked out of
the games or worse.

129
00:08:53,125 --> 00:08:55,291
Yeah. As a matter of fact,
the old guy's daughter,

130
00:08:55,375 --> 00:08:58,375
Minerva, was saying something
almost exactly like that.

131
00:08:58,458 --> 00:09:00,833
I can't believe you'd
be that much of an idiot!

132
00:09:00,916 --> 00:09:03,166
Do you even have a
brain in your head?

133
00:09:03,250 --> 00:09:05,500
Obviously not!
Tell him, Gray!

134
00:09:05,583 --> 00:09:07,750
If he doesn't listen,
you can beat it into him!

135
00:09:07,833 --> 00:09:09,541
You need to stop and
think before you ever try

136
00:09:09,625 --> 00:09:11,583
to pull another
crazy stunt like that!

137
00:09:11,666 --> 00:09:13,166
I mean, why do you
get to have all the fun?

138
00:09:13,250 --> 00:09:15,583
I would've loved to beat
the snot outta those guys!

139
00:09:15,666 --> 00:09:18,000
[LUCY] You totally
missed the point!

140
00:09:18,083 --> 00:09:19,375
I know you both
have your reasons

141
00:09:19,458 --> 00:09:20,916
for being angry with them,

142
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:24,041
but you have to save it for
the competition, you understand?

143
00:09:24,125 --> 00:09:26,041
I wouldn't have
ever hurt anybody.

144
00:09:26,125 --> 00:09:27,916
I just wanted to get
in that pretty boy's face

145
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:30,250
and let him know I ain't
losing to him again.

146
00:09:30,333 --> 00:09:32,708
Maybe just scare
him a little bit!

147
00:09:32,791 --> 00:09:35,541
Anyway, they are gonna
pay for what they did.

148
00:09:35,625 --> 00:09:37,625
Being in a guild with
somebody means that you never

149
00:09:37,708 --> 00:09:40,083
turn your back on them,
no matter what.

150
00:09:40,166 --> 00:09:42,833
There's a big difference
between strict and cruel.

151
00:09:42,916 --> 00:09:44,583
I would say they crossed
the line with the way

152
00:09:44,666 --> 00:09:46,500
they treated that
poor girl this evening.

153
00:09:46,583 --> 00:09:48,125
Completely uncalled for.

154
00:09:48,208 --> 00:09:49,833
After she was
humiliated like that,

155
00:09:49,916 --> 00:09:51,541
she still came over
here and tried to give me

156
00:09:51,625 --> 00:09:54,791
her Celestial gate keys
as an act of kindness.

157
00:09:54,875 --> 00:09:57,666
I wonder if she even
has anywhere else to go.

158
00:09:57,750 --> 00:09:59,750
I'm worried about her.

159
00:09:59,833 --> 00:10:04,250
Well she can't ever go back
to her guild, that's for sure.

160
00:10:04,333 --> 00:10:07,625
Those bastards. How can they
treat somebody like that?

161
00:10:07,708 --> 00:10:09,583
Screw the games, I'm goin' back!

162
00:10:09,666 --> 00:10:10,958
[GRAY] Alright! Count me in!

163
00:10:11,041 --> 00:10:13,166
Are both of you that stupid?

164
00:10:13,250 --> 00:10:14,666
[WENDY] You need
to do like Erza said

165
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:16,333
and settle the
score in the games!

166
00:10:16,416 --> 00:10:18,250
And now that this foolishness
has happened tonight,

167
00:10:18,333 --> 00:10:20,625
we can rightfully expect that
every member of Sabertooth

168
00:10:20,708 --> 00:10:23,625
will have a personal
vendetta against our guild!

169
00:10:26,541 --> 00:10:28,750
[ERZA] It's natural
that everyone competing,

170
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:31,000
regardless of their affiliation,

171
00:10:31,083 --> 00:10:34,625
brings their own motivations
and emotions into the arena.

172
00:10:42,916 --> 00:10:44,541
So ya wanna
play tough, do ya?

173
00:10:44,625 --> 00:10:45,833
You're never
gonna stop us!

174
00:10:45,916 --> 00:10:47,250
Would you guys quit
screwin' around?

175
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:48,625
Uh!

176
00:10:48,708 --> 00:10:51,458
This is a serious situation--

177
00:10:51,541 --> 00:10:53,500
[ALL] Uh.

178
00:10:55,833 --> 00:10:57,833
The next person
that hits me...

179
00:10:57,916 --> 00:10:59,333
[ERZA] is dead!

180
00:10:59,416 --> 00:11:01,250
[NATSU and GRAY] Sorry, Ma'am!

181
00:11:09,250 --> 00:11:10,416
[MALE CITIZEN 166D]
Did you hear what happened?

182
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:11,708
[MALE CITIZEN 166E]
You mean last night?

183
00:11:11,791 --> 00:11:12,916
[FEMALE CITIZEN 166A]
What was it?

184
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,666
Some nutjob went
over to the inn where

185
00:11:14,750 --> 00:11:17,750
Sabertooth is staying and just
started tearing up the place.

186
00:11:17,833 --> 00:11:19,166
What kind of idiot
would pick a fight

187
00:11:19,250 --> 00:11:21,416
with those guys?
Must have a death wish.

188
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:23,916
[BOTH laughing]

189
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:25,333
[MALE CITIZEN 166D]
I know, right?

190
00:11:25,416 --> 00:11:26,208
[FEMALE CITIZEN 166A] There's
always fights and stuff

191
00:11:26,291 --> 00:11:27,541
outside the tournament.

192
00:11:27,625 --> 00:11:28,875
[MALE CITIZEN 166E] Yeah,
well they need to do it

193
00:11:28,958 --> 00:11:30,625
out on the street and
entertain the rest of us.

194
00:11:30,708 --> 00:11:32,791
[MALE and FEMALE CITIZEN laugh]

195
00:11:34,041 --> 00:11:35,708
[YUKINO] Was it Natsu?

196
00:11:37,458 --> 00:11:40,083
[NATSU] Any guild
that makes a friend cry...

197
00:11:40,166 --> 00:11:42,791
doesn't get to
call itself a guild!

198
00:11:45,833 --> 00:11:48,541
[YUKINO] No way. Wow.

199
00:11:48,625 --> 00:11:56,541
♪

200
00:11:56,625 --> 00:11:59,250
Welcome to day three
of the Grand Magic Games!

201
00:11:59,333 --> 00:12:00,958
That puts us at
the halfway point.

202
00:12:01,041 --> 00:12:03,208
How are we ever going to
top the dramatic fights

203
00:12:03,291 --> 00:12:05,458
and eye candy of
the last two days?

204
00:12:05,541 --> 00:12:08,875
I personally, will be on my best
behavior around today's guest.

205
00:12:08,958 --> 00:12:11,291
From the Magic Council,
it's Marshal Lahar.

206
00:12:11,375 --> 00:12:13,250
It's been quite a while.

207
00:12:13,333 --> 00:12:15,291
Thank you for
having me here.

208
00:12:15,375 --> 00:12:17,666
As Chief Marshal of the
Custody Enforcement Unit,

209
00:12:17,750 --> 00:12:20,250
your job is catching the
bad guys, isn't that right?

210
00:12:20,333 --> 00:12:23,583
Yes. And let me
remind any would be cheaters

211
00:12:23,666 --> 00:12:25,000
that I'm watching you.

212
00:12:25,083 --> 00:12:27,416
[CROWD laughs]

213
00:12:27,500 --> 00:12:29,875
[CHAPATI] That's right, he's got
eyes in the back of his head,

214
00:12:29,958 --> 00:12:33,083
and he never sleeps,
so no funny stuff!

215
00:12:33,166 --> 00:12:37,416
Damn you, Lahar.
Just had to drag me with you.

216
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:43,208
They want you to be a guest
at the Grand Magic Games?

217
00:12:43,291 --> 00:12:45,000
What'd you tell them?

218
00:12:45,083 --> 00:12:47,375
I told them I'd be happy to.

219
00:12:47,458 --> 00:12:49,916
You should come along
with me. It will be fun.

220
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:52,416
Thanks, but I'll pass.

221
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:53,708
The full ranks of
Fairy Tail will be

222
00:12:53,791 --> 00:12:55,333
participating this year.

223
00:12:55,416 --> 00:12:58,291
Wouldn't you like to see
them all alive and well?

224
00:12:58,375 --> 00:12:59,958
[DORANBOLT] Of course I would.

225
00:13:00,041 --> 00:13:03,166
But, they don't want to see me.

226
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:06,250
[LAHAR] How many times do I have
to tell you, that's in the past?

227
00:13:06,333 --> 00:13:09,125
Besides, you left them
to save your own life.

228
00:13:11,583 --> 00:13:14,083
Everybody is looking
towards the future.

229
00:13:14,166 --> 00:13:16,750
We learn from our
experiences and move ahead.

230
00:13:16,833 --> 00:13:18,583
You should, too.

231
00:13:25,208 --> 00:13:27,166
Oh, no! We're
gonna be so late!

232
00:13:27,250 --> 00:13:29,208
I told you, tomcat,
we didn't have enough time

233
00:13:29,291 --> 00:13:30,625
to stop and buy food!

234
00:13:30,708 --> 00:13:33,208
It just smelled so yummy,
that I couldn't resist it!

235
00:13:33,291 --> 00:13:36,041
[ROMEO] Quit flapping your
gums and move your feet!

236
00:13:38,708 --> 00:13:40,625
[CHAPATI] Let's kick off this
hump day with a game that's

237
00:13:40,708 --> 00:13:45,833
sure to be exciting. One
that we call... Pandemonium!

238
00:13:45,916 --> 00:13:48,208
What the heck's
"pandemonium" mean anyway?

239
00:13:48,291 --> 00:13:51,583
[CARLA] Usually it means chaos
or panic. But sometimes it can

240
00:13:51,666 --> 00:13:54,500
be used to refer to a
den of demons or monsters.

241
00:13:54,583 --> 00:13:56,250
Maybe it'll be set
up like some sort of

242
00:13:56,333 --> 00:13:58,708
haunted house game. The
players walk down a long

243
00:13:58,791 --> 00:14:00,916
dark hallway,
when all of a sudden...

244
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:04,458
A scary ghost
pops out of nowhere!

245
00:14:04,541 --> 00:14:07,541
Whoa. I might be too
scared to even watch this one.

246
00:14:07,625 --> 00:14:10,000
[MAVIS] A game like that
sounds terrifying to me.

247
00:14:10,083 --> 00:14:11,458
[ROMEO, HAPPY, and CARLA] Huh?

248
00:14:11,541 --> 00:14:14,125
No offense, but aren't
you a ghost yourself?

249
00:14:14,208 --> 00:14:16,583
[CHAPATI] As usual, we will
have just one member from

250
00:14:16,666 --> 00:14:19,666
each team competing.
So please choose wisely.

251
00:14:19,750 --> 00:14:22,458
I got this one. I'm
still pretty fired up from

252
00:14:22,541 --> 00:14:24,000
what went down last night.

253
00:14:24,083 --> 00:14:26,375
You did yesterday's round,
so it's not your turn!

254
00:14:26,458 --> 00:14:28,041
Yeah Natsu, you're not
the only one who would

255
00:14:28,125 --> 00:14:30,041
love to get some sweet payback!

256
00:14:30,125 --> 00:14:34,291
Right. So I'll play then.
I'm certain that you'd only

257
00:14:34,375 --> 00:14:37,166
complicate the matter further
if you were to compete.

258
00:14:37,250 --> 00:14:40,250
Alright! Go and
get us a win, Erza!

259
00:14:40,333 --> 00:14:41,625
Yeah, you've got this!

260
00:14:41,708 --> 00:14:43,583
That is so unfair,
I called this one!

261
00:14:43,666 --> 00:14:46,333
The decision's been made,
so would ya shut up?

262
00:14:46,416 --> 00:14:48,708
I think I should be the
one to go in for our team.

263
00:14:48,791 --> 00:14:49,958
Well I think I should.

264
00:14:50,041 --> 00:14:52,708
I gotta redeem
myself after yesterday.

265
00:14:52,791 --> 00:14:54,416
Why are you
here anyway, Cana?

266
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:56,208
I thought you were
a reserve member.

267
00:14:56,291 --> 00:14:58,000
Yeah, what happened
to Mystogan?

268
00:14:58,083 --> 00:15:00,750
I know he's shy but no
one's seen him at all today.

269
00:15:00,833 --> 00:15:03,083
The guest announcer is the
same guy who arrested him,

270
00:15:03,166 --> 00:15:05,583
so he decided to
sit this one out today.

271
00:15:05,666 --> 00:15:07,541
Makes sense to me.

272
00:15:07,625 --> 00:15:09,708
Hey, if Erzy's gonna be
going in for her team,

273
00:15:09,791 --> 00:15:11,625
I wanna play against her!

274
00:15:11,708 --> 00:15:13,291
Fine, I'll allow it.

275
00:15:15,458 --> 00:15:17,291
[MILLIANNA] Sorry Erzy,
but I'm gonna beat ya!

276
00:15:17,375 --> 00:15:18,708
That so?

277
00:15:18,791 --> 00:15:21,458
I have never stopped
hating Jellal.

278
00:15:21,541 --> 00:15:23,416
[MILLIANNA]
He used us like tools.

279
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:25,791
He took Simon away from us.

280
00:15:25,875 --> 00:15:30,458
For all those sins...
he has to pay!

281
00:15:33,291 --> 00:15:35,125
[ERZA] I mustn't lose focus!

282
00:15:35,208 --> 00:15:37,458
[CHAPATI] Putting her paws onto
the field for Mermaid Heel,

283
00:15:37,541 --> 00:15:38,875
it's Millianna!

284
00:15:38,958 --> 00:15:40,333
Hey, I remember her!

285
00:15:40,416 --> 00:15:41,500
So do I.

286
00:15:41,583 --> 00:15:43,583
I guess she was the
one wearin' the hood.

287
00:15:43,666 --> 00:15:45,791
So she finally
joined a guild?

288
00:15:45,875 --> 00:15:48,541
[ALEXEI] The Council is
watching, so be careful

289
00:15:48,625 --> 00:15:51,125
not to draw their
attention, Obra.

290
00:15:52,833 --> 00:15:54,750
I should go. For my fans.

291
00:15:54,833 --> 00:15:56,333
[FEMALE CROWD cheers]

292
00:15:56,416 --> 00:15:58,958
I said that I was gonna
take this one last night.

293
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:01,166
I'll give them all a
taste of my Black Lightning

294
00:16:01,250 --> 00:16:02,750
they're never gonna forget!

295
00:16:02,833 --> 00:16:04,416
Try not to get
ahead of yourself.

296
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:06,916
We don't even know
what this game entails.

297
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:08,541
[RUFUS chuckles]

298
00:16:08,625 --> 00:16:10,291
[STING] It doesn't
matter to me.

299
00:16:10,375 --> 00:16:14,541
If Natsu's not competing, then
I don't really care who goes.

300
00:16:17,416 --> 00:16:19,125
Jura's gonna
play in this round?

301
00:16:19,208 --> 00:16:21,708
It's what the
hag wanted, so yes.

302
00:16:21,791 --> 00:16:23,208
My poor sock.

303
00:16:23,291 --> 00:16:25,208
Just buy a new one, dummy!

304
00:16:26,416 --> 00:16:28,166
[JURA] Victory is mine.

305
00:16:28,250 --> 00:16:30,291
[CHAPATI] All of the
competitors have been chosen!

306
00:16:30,375 --> 00:16:34,458
From Sabertooth, Olga!
From Lamia Scale, Jura!

307
00:16:34,541 --> 00:16:38,666
From Blue Pegasus, Hibiki!
From Raven Tail, Obra!

308
00:16:38,750 --> 00:16:40,750
From Mermaid Heel, Millianna!

309
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:43,083
From Quatro Puppy, Novali!

310
00:16:43,166 --> 00:16:47,416
From Fairy Tail A, Erza!
From Fairy Tail B, Cana!

311
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:49,916
Let's all give them a big
round of applause, folks!

312
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:55,083
[CROWD cheering]

313
00:16:55,166 --> 00:17:06,000
♪

314
00:17:06,083 --> 00:17:07,250
What is this?

315
00:17:07,333 --> 00:17:08,916
I don't know.

316
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:16,125
[HIBIKI] I'll see what
Archive brings up.

317
00:17:19,166 --> 00:17:21,958
[explosion or rumble]

318
00:17:27,208 --> 00:17:29,000
[MATO] Before you
stands a castle filled with

319
00:17:29,083 --> 00:17:32,166
vicious monsters.
That's Pandemonium!

320
00:17:32,250 --> 00:17:34,625
Holy crap!

321
00:17:34,708 --> 00:17:37,125
I take it we're to do
battle with these monsters?

322
00:17:37,208 --> 00:17:39,750
[MATO]
Yes! You are correct, sir!

323
00:17:39,833 --> 00:17:41,083
[CROWD gasps]

324
00:17:41,166 --> 00:17:43,041
[MATO] One hundred
terrifying beasts are lurking

325
00:17:43,125 --> 00:17:44,500
within the castle walls.

326
00:17:44,583 --> 00:17:46,416
But don't panic,
there's no danger of them

327
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:48,125
escaping and
attacking the crowd.

328
00:17:48,208 --> 00:17:51,541
They're magical projections we
created solely for this game!

329
00:17:51,625 --> 00:17:54,166
They are classified by
their degree of difficulty.

330
00:17:54,250 --> 00:17:58,708
We have five classes:
D, C, B, A, and S!

331
00:17:58,791 --> 00:18:01,375
The distribution
breakdown is shown here.

332
00:18:01,458 --> 00:18:03,791
To give you an example,
let me show you how strong

333
00:18:03,875 --> 00:18:07,500
a D-Class monster is!
They're the weakest, remember.

334
00:18:07,583 --> 00:18:09,041
[chuckles]

335
00:18:16,666 --> 00:18:18,541
[screaming]

336
00:18:24,666 --> 00:18:26,708
[MATO] The Pandemonium castle
is filled to the brim with

337
00:18:26,791 --> 00:18:30,125
these vile creatures and many
more that are far stronger!

338
00:18:30,208 --> 00:18:32,875
One hundred monsters await you!

339
00:18:34,125 --> 00:18:36,916
I know he said that they
were all magical projections,

340
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:39,833
but they can probably still
hurt people, can't they?

341
00:18:39,916 --> 00:18:42,291
I just hope Erza and
Cana come out unscathed.

342
00:18:42,375 --> 00:18:44,333
I'm pretty sure they can
take care of themselves,

343
00:18:44,416 --> 00:18:45,791
but it's still scary.

344
00:18:45,875 --> 00:18:48,625
All these games just get
more and more extravagant!

345
00:18:48,708 --> 00:18:51,791
It's a little too much,
if you want my opinion.

346
00:18:51,875 --> 00:18:55,208
[CROWD chatter]

347
00:18:55,291 --> 00:18:57,500
[MATO] Monsters of a higher
class are two times stronger

348
00:18:57,583 --> 00:18:58,833
than the ones beneath them.

349
00:18:58,916 --> 00:19:01,583
So if you think that
D-class guy looked nasty,

350
00:19:01,666 --> 00:19:05,083
you'll lose your mind when the
S-class rears its ugly head.

351
00:19:05,166 --> 00:19:08,458
I'm not even sure that a Wizard
Saint could beat one of those.

352
00:19:08,541 --> 00:19:09,875
Hm.

353
00:19:09,958 --> 00:19:11,958
[MATO] You will all take
turns in choosing the number

354
00:19:12,041 --> 00:19:14,458
of monsters that you
wish to fight in each round.

355
00:19:14,541 --> 00:19:17,750
We call this, the competitor's
"right to challenge."

356
00:19:17,833 --> 00:19:20,083
So we make the choice?

357
00:19:20,166 --> 00:19:21,666
[MATO] That is correct!

358
00:19:21,750 --> 00:19:24,416
So, for instance, if you say you
want to fight three monsters,

359
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:27,958
then, lo and behold, there will
be three waiting inside for you.

360
00:19:28,041 --> 00:19:30,250
You will go in alone, of course.

361
00:19:30,333 --> 00:19:32,791
If you successfully vanquish
those three creatures,

362
00:19:32,875 --> 00:19:36,083
you will then be
awarded three points!

363
00:19:36,166 --> 00:19:39,375
The next competitor in the
rotation will choose a number

364
00:19:39,458 --> 00:19:42,458
out of the ninety-seven that
still remain to challenge.

365
00:19:42,541 --> 00:19:44,625
And then the process repeats!

366
00:19:44,708 --> 00:19:47,083
The game will end when
either all the monsters

367
00:19:47,166 --> 00:19:49,416
[MATO] have been cleared,
or at the point that everyone

368
00:19:49,500 --> 00:19:52,666
runs out of magic power;
whichever comes first.

369
00:19:52,750 --> 00:19:54,875
So there's some
math involved, huh?

370
00:19:54,958 --> 00:19:56,250
[MATO] Yes, to a degree.

371
00:19:56,333 --> 00:19:58,666
After the first round,
choosing your numbers wisely

372
00:19:58,750 --> 00:20:00,625
will become a
bit more important.

373
00:20:00,708 --> 00:20:02,375
But you'd do
well to remember that

374
00:20:02,458 --> 00:20:05,750
not all of these monsters
are created equal.

375
00:20:05,833 --> 00:20:07,125
[MATO] Whether you
choose to test your skills

376
00:20:07,208 --> 00:20:09,583
against five monsters,
or only one,

377
00:20:09,666 --> 00:20:13,208
they will be chosen
completely at random.

378
00:20:13,291 --> 00:20:15,250
So that means we'll
have to strategize

379
00:20:15,333 --> 00:20:17,208
and use our heads to
try to avoid going against

380
00:20:17,291 --> 00:20:19,416
the S-class guys in there.

381
00:20:19,500 --> 00:20:21,708
He just told us that they're
gonna be chosen at random,

382
00:20:21,791 --> 00:20:24,750
so how the hell can you
use any kind of strategy?

383
00:20:25,458 --> 00:20:27,875
You can't. But I sure can.

384
00:20:27,958 --> 00:20:29,875
I know all about probability.

385
00:20:29,958 --> 00:20:32,375
And my Archive magic
will come in handy.

386
00:20:32,458 --> 00:20:33,958
[MATO] Although the
higher-ranked creatures

387
00:20:34,041 --> 00:20:36,625
are more difficult, points
are determined solely by

388
00:20:36,708 --> 00:20:38,875
the number of monsters
you can defeat.

389
00:20:38,958 --> 00:20:41,041
[MATO] Once you enter
the castle, you will not

390
00:20:41,125 --> 00:20:43,041
be allowed to leave
until you've successfully

391
00:20:43,125 --> 00:20:44,791
completed your challenge.

392
00:20:44,875 --> 00:20:46,541
[CANA] So what happens if
you don't beat all of them

393
00:20:46,625 --> 00:20:48,208
and get knocked out inside?

394
00:20:48,291 --> 00:20:50,083
[MATO] You'll keep all
the points you accumulated

395
00:20:50,166 --> 00:20:51,458
in the previous rounds.

396
00:20:51,541 --> 00:20:53,208
But you'll also
be out of the game.

397
00:20:53,291 --> 00:20:55,666
No points will be awarded
if you beat less than

398
00:20:55,750 --> 00:20:57,916
the number you
challenged that round.

399
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:59,875
It would seem that
not getting overzealous

400
00:20:59,958 --> 00:21:01,875
with your challenges is key.

401
00:21:01,958 --> 00:21:04,041
But if you only fight
one monster in every round

402
00:21:04,125 --> 00:21:06,166
there's no way that
you can get ahead.

403
00:21:06,250 --> 00:21:08,500
And they also need to
factor in how much magic power

404
00:21:08,583 --> 00:21:10,958
they'll be able to
recover between each round.

405
00:21:11,041 --> 00:21:13,833
This game is way more
complicated than it seems.

406
00:21:13,916 --> 00:21:17,041
I'm curious to see how many
our members will choose.

407
00:21:17,125 --> 00:21:20,125
I think they'll both
do a really good job.

408
00:21:20,208 --> 00:21:22,208
[MATO] Now, to decide
the order you'll go in,

409
00:21:22,291 --> 00:21:25,500
I'd like everyone
to please draw a straw!

410
00:21:25,583 --> 00:21:26,958
[beep]

411
00:21:28,166 --> 00:21:30,375
I'm going first!

412
00:21:30,458 --> 00:21:32,416
Man you're lucky.
And I'd be willing to bet

413
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:35,083
that means you'll also get
the most amount of turns.

414
00:21:35,166 --> 00:21:38,708
Meanwhile, I'll be
stuck back at number eight.

415
00:21:38,791 --> 00:21:41,541
[ERZA] Interesting. I had
assumed victory in this event

416
00:21:41,625 --> 00:21:43,958
relied entirely on
the luck of the draw.

417
00:21:44,041 --> 00:21:45,416
[MATO] It's far more than that.

418
00:21:45,500 --> 00:21:47,250
You have to consider pacing,
your opponents' strength,

419
00:21:47,333 --> 00:21:49,333
the likelihood of getting
a really nasty monster.

420
00:21:49,416 --> 00:21:50,708
The list goes on and on.

421
00:21:50,791 --> 00:21:53,458
It is quite a complex
game if you think about it.

422
00:21:53,541 --> 00:21:57,500
No. In fact, this is
no longer even a game.

423
00:21:59,250 --> 00:22:00,791
[MATO] Huh?

424
00:22:04,708 --> 00:22:08,791
Inside this castle...
wait one hundred monsters.

425
00:22:08,875 --> 00:22:11,625
I choose to challenge...

426
00:22:11,708 --> 00:22:13,708
all of them!

427
00:22:13,791 --> 00:22:15,208
[MILLIANA gasps]

428
00:22:15,291 --> 00:22:16,291
[CANA, HIBIKI, and NOVALI] Huh?

429
00:22:16,375 --> 00:22:17,958
[MATO] Say what?

430
00:22:19,666 --> 00:22:25,458
[ALL gasp]

431
00:22:25,541 --> 00:22:28,458
[BOTH laughing]

432
00:24:12,666 --> 00:24:15,750
[NATSU] Erza is one scary chick!
One hundred monsters on her own?

433
00:24:15,833 --> 00:24:17,916
[HAPPY] Well, she's kind of
a monster herself, isn't she?

434
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:19,791
[NATSU]
Whoa, she's got tons of armor!

435
00:24:19,875 --> 00:24:22,083
[HAPPY] Heaven's Wheel,
Black Wing, Flame Empress,

436
00:24:22,166 --> 00:24:25,666
Sea Empress, Flight,
Adamantine, Giant, Morning Star.

437
00:24:25,750 --> 00:24:26,958
[NATSU] Ya think
she's got Troll Armor

438
00:24:27,041 --> 00:24:28,541
and Wicked Witch Armor, too?

439
00:24:28,625 --> 00:24:30,958
[HAPPY] That kinda sounds
like you're makin' fun of her.

440
00:24:31,041 --> 00:24:33,750
[HAPPY and NATSU] Next time:
"One Hundred Against One!"

441
00:24:33,833 --> 00:24:35,291
[HAPPY] I wonder if
the other guys are sad

442
00:24:35,375 --> 00:24:37,208
that they don't get
to fight any monsters.

443
00:24:37,291 --> 00:24:38,583
[NATSU] I dunno.
They'll probably get over it

444
00:24:38,666 --> 00:24:40,041
pretty quickly.

